author: Yingying Chen
text: Literally the best AF in this area!!! Great glutes machines, upp body machines, they even have a hair dryer and sanitary pads üò≠üò≠ ‚Ä¶

author: Roger Thomas Tan
text: This is a rather big gym and I have seen bigger gyms before BUT this gym though just only relatively big is packed with weights and machines! That‚Äôs so awesome! They have two Smith machines, three squats machines, one tricep dip machine (how often do you see that?), one chest pull over machine (I didn‚Äôt even know they have machines for pull over), TWO free weights area! They absolutely utilised the space fully yet without feeling crampy! They even have a small room for aerobic classes and a few machines for cardio! So even though there are a handful of other patrons around BUT the numerous machines around means you don‚Äôt have to share or wait for machines/ weights! This is really a great place to work out! Many machines and free weights to use and it‚Äôs just beside the MRT station. Parking can be done in the shopping centre! I‚Äôd recommend this place to gym if you are in upper Bukit Timah area!

author: Jeremy Lim
text: Despite the ratings, I feel that this is still a decent outlet. There is a big crowd but it has 3 squat racks and tons of machines. Perhaps less spacious and open than other outlets.

author: Jayvinn Wong
text:
Came back 1 year after my previous visit, was pleasantly surprised to see that they have renovated the premises! The shower area and overall cleanliness have also greatly improved.

There is a very large range of machine and plate loaded equipment.

Notably:
2 Smith machines
2 Full racks
1 Half rack
1 Deadlift platform
Iso lateral high row (plate loaded)
Pullover machine (plate loaded)
Dip machine
Hack squat (plate loaded)
Leg press (plate loaded)
Stairmaster
3 x treadmills

author: Arya Ng
text: One of the nicest Anytime Fitness Gym in Singapore despite some members bring in and put on their tripod during exercise. Firstly,  its may blocking the way round gym with tripod legs wide open. Secondly, you may recording other members which is disrespectful to others privacy. Especially on weekend morning there are members with tripod . Cheers!

author: Golden Rays c
text: this gym is small but has all u need, including a nice little studio fr u to do stretching/warm up/cool down with mirrors and fans too. the music also improved, previously they kept playing the same few melo songs but now it's more uplifting. hope they refresh the music regularly!!

author: tan jun heng
text:
I've been a long-time member of Anytime Fitness Bukit Timah and have always had a great experience. The gym is well-equipped and provides a perfect environment for my workouts. Special thanks to Shermaine, Eugene, and Jennifer for their exceptional support and service. Shermaine's friendly nature, Eugene's expert guidance, and Jennifer's positive attitude have made my fitness journey enjoyable. Highly recommended!

---

author: Yichao Teoh
text: Huge branch with the friendliest staffs. Shoutout to eric for his help and advice.

author: Tabasco Guzzler
text: Good, well-spaced range of equipment, youthful vibe mostly folks in their twenties. Management, please place a few clothing hooks & a simple rack in the changing room, so we can hang our bags etc. Currently it's just a tiny bare room with nowhere to put our things while changing.

author: Thorvald Kleve
text:
I recently joined this Anytime Fitness branch. Initially, I was quite happy, but they‚Äôve now closed for a month due to renovations ‚Äî without any prior notification or offer of a refund.

When I raised this with the management, they told me I could have frozen my membership, but since they only posted a notice on social media (which I didn‚Äôt see), I missed the chance to do so. They also suggested I use another branch, but I specifically chose this location for its convenience, so that's not a viable option.

In short, while the gym itself is fine, the customer service has been very disappointing.

author: Wei Yang
text: spacious with new equipment but god it is messy and littered with tissues and empty plastic bottles. no one puts back their weights here too

author: Paul Lee
text:
Been a member for roughly 10 years. I wrote in to cancel my membership via email, after being directed from their staff on their WhatsApp chat with instructions to cancel. They acknowledged my membership cancellation and asked me the reason of my cancellation, which is tbh none of their business, and so I didn‚Äôt reply. A cancellation email is a cancellation email, I don‚Äôt need to explain myself.

The club automatically renewed my membership fee for months until I realised it in my bank statements. They refused to refund the money - I was lucky to have caught it early on, or else they would have charged me indefinitely. Feeling quite dismayed especially being a longtime AFBT gym-goer.

author: Michael
text:
I‚Äôve always appreciated how Anytime Fitness promotes itself as being a part of the community. However, I‚Äôm deeply disappointed with the branch at Bukit Timah Shopping Centre. It seems that the business owners here are more focused on profits than truly caring for the community they‚Äôre part of.

The poorly waterproofed toilets have caused significant damage to tenants downstairs, with water leaks and even ceilings falling. This isn‚Äôt just an inconvenience; it‚Äôs a serious issue affecting the livelihoods of other businesses.

As a brand that prides itself on community, I urge you to take responsibility and fix this problem promptly. Please show that you care for the people and businesses around you, not just your own bottom line.

author: Dev Kumar
text: Definitely has all the fan favorite machines in the house like hack squat, low row  stair master , hyperextension etc but extremely poor wifi reception even when the gym is empty and the machines are very worn out and rusty. Wish they could do a luxurious Refresh because beauty world is meant to represent upper class and also there‚Äôs many celebrities and influencers that come here. Very tight space at the dumbbell area as well. Shower facilities are great but there should be one dedicated DRY changing room. There should be more CCTV cameras to cover every area of the gym very clearly cause I know there isn‚Äôt one monitoring the charging point which is the most high risk area.

author: Jin Kahn Lee
text:
I recently returned to Singapore for a duration and was looking for a fitness solution nearby. As a first time customer, this has to be one of the worst experiences I‚Äôve had dealing with appalling and unprofessional service.

After submitting a query on pricing and membership, I was informed via email that a member of staff would contact me shortly after. I never received the call back, failing which I attempted to contact the number that was provided. After numerous failed attempts and rejected calls, I decided to head down in person to make the inquiry, only to be turned away at the entrance by a staff member who was rude and irritable.

Needless to say, I wouldn‚Äôt recommend anyone wasting their time and money on a subpar business that doesn‚Äôt seem interested in treating new customers with respect or sincerity.

author: Linda Lee
text:
I enjoyed the various sessions almost daiily because  it instilled in me discipline to workout . My energy level has improved and I felt healthier and stronger.  This has also impacted and improved my daily life as I could perform more chores without difficulties
I hope the gym will continue to support these daily sessions as it encourages many people to stay healthy and fit.

author: Sze Chuan Tan
text:
Decent gym in terms of size and availability of equipment.

Reviews about its run-downness is true, I didn't really mind so long things are working properly. I would have given a 4-star but...

I have to knock away 2 stars because of some safety issues. One very big minus point is the wear and tear that can potentially cause injury to users. For example, I tried using a wrist strap to a cable machine and it came off while I was pulling heavy weight. Then I realised the velcro was so worn out that it couldn't be secured properly.

Another minus point is having the power racks with the pull-up bars just directly below the beams of light. Tried to do pull-ups and a beam hit my head because I didn't expect an obstruction in the way.

author: Daniel Cheong
text: Good and friendly service from staff. Gym is nicely equipped and convenient location. Just signed up so looking forward to use it.

author: Shakir Ahmed
text:
I was interested in a monthly membership. The fee was high but was still worth due to 24hr access. However, the registration fee is very high as well as a stupid key fob fee. I couldn't understand at this day and age, why the key fob fee isn't made to be paid as a deposit refundable upon membership termination and returning the key. It's such a stupid business decision.

What am I going to do with the key fob after I end membership? Hang it on my wall as a precious item, sell it or play with it? It's a complete waste of resources and disregard towards sustainability.

There are plenty of gyms around as good as AF or better in terms of equipment but with sensible pricing, so I think they're shooting themselves in the foot.

author: Marcus Yap
text:
Although showing abit of age, this gym is comprehensive with friendly and helpful staff and fellow patrons.
One observation to note is the marked increase in patrons within the past year(nearly 2-3 times) due to new developments in the area. Furthermore, with up and coming condos in the vincinity expected to TOP within the year and next alone adding a further ~1200units in the area, this outlet is going to get really crowded in the near future. Franchise owner gonna huat big time.

author: Khor Le Yi
text:
I come here for classes every week! They have the best variety of classes to choose from. Highly recommend the TRX, HIIT, Pilates, Yoga classes, all of which I sign up for every week.

The community is great and the class instructors push me to improve every time. When I first joined, I could barely do a push-up! Now it's much easier than before.

I highly encourage anyone who's looking to get regular exercises to join. These are exercises that I'll never do if I were exercising alone.

author: Cassie Zhuang
text: The place and the facilities are very old and worse than activesg gyms and other AF outlets at cc. They enforce a very strict dress code when working out there without clear notices posted in the gym. I was warned by a trainer (he called himself Golden) from the gym who didn‚Äôt show clear identification at first, but only told the name aft was asked, and he tried to educate me with common sense and said the requirements abt the dress code was stated in the contract). I can‚Äôt believe this is their service standard which is worse than other branches. Actually I feel it doesn‚Äôt make sense that they allow people wearing flip flops but only block people wearing cotton shorts. To be honest, the experience there is not even worth one star.

author: Pam Sekhon
text:
Nice gym.  Everyone is helpful.
Brought my daughter down to join was assisted by friendly Jennifer. She was helpful and very patient in explaining the details of the membership.

author: United we are
text: Had stopped training for a very Long time for various reasons. Early January this year decided to give it a shot again. Since then have always enjoyed my workouts, always enjoyed the warm welcome from the staff. One of the few gyms I have been to where staff is More than happy to help with lifts. This place has come to feel like a family. Without hesitation you should definitely come and workout here. Go AFBT!!!!!!!

author: Hasif Styles
text: Very friendly and accommodating staffs. The gym looks pretty spacious to perform my workouts in well equipped with toilets for comfort.

text: Slightly larger than your average anytime fitness gyms, but not the best I've been to (Yishun holds that honor). There is only one deadlift station but they have a kicking bag and a generous stretching area

text: Been to quite a few anytime fitness branches and this is the worst smelling one (it‚Äôs a mix of extremely strong cologne/ deodorant and sweat smell) - you can smell it before even entering the gym and once you go in, you will soak up and reek of the smell and it lingers after showering at times.

author: Lee Ming Han

author: Zhi Yu Teh
text: Very well equipped gym with one deadlift platform, and two squat racks. Contains a plethora of machines and farmer handles for farmer walks (which is a rarity in Singapore). Super polite and friendly staff. Most importantly, a punching bag in a room which very little people can peek into, perfect if you wish to start kickboxing as cardio but is afraid of being seen.

author: Jo Lee

Best Anytime Fitness in town!
Instructor Shermine is passionate, knowledgeable and tenacious in supporting your fitness journey. Highly recommended!!! üòçüòçüòç ‚Ä¶

author: Dr Dru
text: 3 half-racks. 1 Smith machine. 1 oly platform. Very very old rubberized weights. No decent bars. Pretty warm gym without decent ventilation. Ho-hum...

author: Ernest
text: Excellent gym! Went to their classes for a few months. Good environment, relatively clean.

author: Kenny Seong
text:
If I can, I could even not give a star at all. All because of the trainers there. I went to this branch a few time and the last visit I was there, I wanted to ask 1 of the trainer on the ground, Gordon, who was rather free at that point of time on the studio classes schedule and attempted to get his attention by waving and call out to him while was walking towards him, our eyes met yet this Gordon pretended not seeing me and quickly walked away! So I was ignored because he knows I'm a member from another branch and chose to treat me as invisible.

What a customer service you have there, Gordon! Well done! Winning competition is nothing when your nose is so high up in the sky.

2ndly, is the former trainer Wilson (if I remember correctly), short and wear specs. 1 of the most arrogant ego trainer I have ever seen, ask him on certain machine yet he direct me to Gordon and some other regulars there while he himself was just pacing up and down for nothing and as Gordon being himself, walks away and act busy. Lol! What worse was Wilson monopolized the equipment when he and his client was using it! And I was to rush my sets just to let him use as he was standing damn near staring!

Not to mention this 2 clowns even tease their own studio classes' instructors and participants. I walked past them once and they were talking loudly with their friend and mentioned about Zumba class is a joke and ineffective and dont understand why people are still attending it, maybe being stupid.

This branch has the worst trainers I have ever encountered. Not going back to this branch anymore and definitely not recommending to any of my friends.

If you are the owner reading this, probably it's time to educate them or rather, for your gym's sake, sack them.

text: Decent Anytime Fitness with plenty of equipment. It even has a laying down hamstring curl machine and a seated Hip abductor. It's quite hidden in the basement, but can get crowded around lunch and dinner time.
